Good evening, and welcome to our daily roundup of the latest developments on the coronavirus pandemic in Australia.
The federal government will give the allowance to businesses and not-for-profit organisations that have taken a 30% hit to turnover because of the coronavirus.
Payments will flow to businesses in the first week of May, with the program to start from 30 March.
Western Australia and Tasmania have said they will enforce the new limits, while Queensland, New South Wales, Victoria and the Australian Capital Territory have gone further.
“We completely understand travellers are a high risk – we are 100% for quarantining,” Paula’s daughter, Olivia, told Guardian Australia.